<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25717</anchor> <rss>anon.180.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.180</addr>  <route>anon.180.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>As <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link> with some centre <tex>a:A</tex>, we have for any <tex>x,y:A</tex> identifications <tex>\chi _x  \colon  a = x</tex> and <tex>\chi _y \colon  a = y</tex>. Therefore, we identify <tex>x</tex> with <tex>y</tex> using <tex>\chi _x ^{-1}   \cdot   \chi _y</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25718</anchor> <rss>erct-001K.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001K</addr>  <route>erct-001K.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">Contractible</link> types are <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">propositions</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001K.agda" type="external">erct-001K.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If a type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link>, then it is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   
 
</mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25719</anchor> <rss>erct-001H.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001H</addr>  <route>erct-001H.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Contractibility</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001H.agda" type="external">erct-001H.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is said to be <em><strong>contractible with centre <tex>a:A</tex></strong></em> when every <tex>x:A</tex> is equipped with an identification <tex>\chi _x \colon  a = x</tex>. We say that <tex>A</tex> is <em><strong>contractible</strong></em> when it comes equipped with some <tex>a:A</tex> such that <tex>A</tex> is contractible with centre <tex>a</tex>. We sometimes refer to a contractible type as a <em><strong>singleton</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks/> <references/></backmatter></tree>